comments:
The current implementation of BirtComp.anyOf() accepts two argument, the first one is the value to be tested, the second one is an array which contain a group of values in which the first argument will be compared against.

In your case, the script can be defined as follows:

array = new Array(2);
array[1] = "Shipped";
array[2] = "Disputed";
BirtComp.anyOf( row["STATUS"] , array );

This implementation is however a bit different from that of spec, that is, BirtComp.anyOf(val, r1, [r2?, rn]).
